 const posts = (await getCollection('blog')).sort(
	(a, b) => a.data.pubDate.valueOf() - b.data.pubDate.valueOf()
);


---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead title={SITE_TITLE} description={SITE_DESCRIPTION} />
		<style>
			main {
				width: 960px;
			}
			section {
				padding: 1rem;
				border-radius: 12px;
				margin-bottom: 2rem;
				box-shadow: 0 2px 5px var(--box-shadow);
			}

			section h2 {
				font-size: 2rem;
				color: var(--text-color);
				margin-bottom: 1rem;
			}

			.instructions {
				text-align: left;
			}

			.instructions p {
				margin-bottom: 1rem;
				font-size: 1.2rem;
				line-height: 1.6;
			}

			.instructions summary {
				font-weight: bold;
				font-size: 1.5rem;
				cursor: pointer;
				margin-top: 1rem;
				color: var(--text-color);
			}

			.instructions details {
				margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
				padding: 1rem;
				border-radius: 8px;
				border: 1px solid rgb(var(--gray));
				text-align: left;
				box-shadow: 0 2px 4px var(--box-shadow);
			}

			.instructions summary:hover {
				color: var(--hover-color);
			}

			.instructions ul {
				list-style: none;
				padding: 0;
			}

			.instructions li {
				margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
				font-size: 1.1rem;
				color: var(--text-color);
			}

			ul {
				display: flex;
				flex-wrap: wrap;
				gap: 2rem;
				list-style-type: none;
				margin: 0;
				padding: 0;
			}
			ul li {
				width: calc(23% - 1rem);
			}
			ul li * {
				text-decoration: none;
				transition: 0.2s ease;
			}
			/* ul li:first-child {
				width: 100%;
				margin-bottom: 1rem;
				text-align: center;
			}
			ul li:first-child img {
				width: 100%;
			}
			ul li:first-child .title {
				font-size: 2.369rem;
			} */
			ul li img {
				margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
				border-radius: 12px;
			}
			ul li a {
				display: block;
			}
			.title {
				margin: 0;
				color: rgb(var(--black));
				line-height: 1;
			}
			.date {
				margin: 0;
				color: rgb(var(--gray));
			}
			ul li a:hover h4,
			ul li a:hover .date {
				color: rgb(var(--accent));
			}
			ul a:hover img {
				box-shadow: var(--box-shadow);
			}
			@media (max-width: 720px) {
				ul {
					gap: 0.5em;
				}
				ul li {
					width: 100%;
					text-align: center;
				}
				/* ul li:first-child {
					margin-bottom: 0;
				}
				ul li:first-child .title {
					font-size: 1.563em;
				} */
			}
		</style>
	</head>
	<body>
		<Header />
		<main>
			<section>
				<h3>EIP research hub</h3>
				<!-- <p class="date"><FormattedDate date={new Date()} /></p> -->
				<p/> 
				This project aims to assist EIP research using Linked Data methods. A dataset containing information about ERC-777 is made available for query with SPARQL locally (available at: (http://localhost:3030/EIPS/sparql).
				</p>
				<p>Check out the resources below to learn how to query this dataset.</p>
			</section>
		
			<section>
				<h5>Highlighted Links</h3>
				<li> 
					ERC-777 dataset with example SPARQL queries publicly available on Github: 
 			<a href="https://github.com/itsnilskerwer/eip-rdf/blob/main/EIPS.ttl">Visit</a>.
			
				</li>	
				<li>
					Source code for the triplification of EIP-related information, written in Java, available on Github:
					<a href="https://github.com/itsnilskerwer/rfc-eth-jakarta">Visit</a>
				</li>
				<li>
					A syntax checker for turtle (copy and paste RDF triples):
					<a href="http://ttl.summerofcode.be">Visit</a>
				</li>
				<li>
					Visualizer (copy and paste RDF triples) by Finish research group: 
					<a href="https://www.ldf.fi/service/rdf-grapher">Visit</a>.
				</li>
			</section>
			
			  
			 <section>
				<h5>Learn about Linked Data keywords:</h5>
				<ul>
					{ posts.map((post) => (
						<li>
							<a href={`/${post.slug}/`}>
								<img width={720} height={360} src={post.data.heroImage} alt="hero image" />
								<h4 class="title">{post.data.title}</h4>
							</a>
						</li>
					))}
				</ul>
			</section> 
			<section>
				<h5>Take part in the A/B Test Protocol:</h5>
				<div class="instructions">
				  <p>First of all, get comfortable with the RDF and SPARQL concepts by reading through the provided Links, Examples and Explainers. 
					The goal of this test is to evaluate the ease of using the ERC-777 dataset as an EIP research tool. 
					ERC-777 is of particular interest to EIP researchers because it defines a token standard used in smart contracts. Since this is used for financial transactions, security is a critical issue. 
					Start by opening one of the Protocols (the order in which Protocols are displayed is randomized to reduce bias). After completing a protocol, click the survey button, to answer some questions anonimously.
				  </p>
				  <details>
					<summary><span class="icon"></span>Instructions for Protocol A</summary>
					<p>The goal of this protocol is to send SPARQL queries to the dataset and answer some questions about ERC-777. 
						If you feel ready, start a 30 min. timer and try to answer the following questions. Note down your answers anywhere e.g. on a piece of paper.
					</p>
					<ul>
					  <li>1. When was ERC-777 first proposed?</li>
					  <li>2. When was this resource moved to status "Final"?</li>
					  <li>3. What was the last update to this EIP resource?</li>
					</ul>
				  </details>
		
				  <details>
					<summary><span class="icon"></span>Instructions for Protocol B</summary>
					<p>The goal of this protocol is for you to use all and any research tools that you usually would, when conducting research. 
						If you feel ready, start a 30 min. timer and try to answer the following questions. Note down your answers anywhere e.g. on a piece of paper.
					</p>
					<ul>
						<li>1. When was ERC-777 first proposed?</li>
						<li>2. When was this resource moved to status "Final"?</li>
						<li>3. What was the last update to this EIP resource?</li>
					</ul>
				  </details>
						</div>
			  </section>
		</main>
		<Footer />
	</body>
</html>
